Re: Could I ask you a favor?
by NileCat » Fri 10.01.2010 11:25 am Thank you everyone for your kind replies and encouragement.I just wanted to say that I didn't want to be a "teacher" here. As I am Japanese and this forum is for Japanese learners, I often stand on the side of answerers though, I know all of you can be my teachers potentially. Regarding my self-study, this forum is like a paradise to me. Because I might be able to be helpful for someone through my studying English here! So, please feel free to point out my mistakes, not only grammar errors but also like going "your explanation doesn't make sense" or "it sounds weird in English". I have a feeling that some of you have overestimated my English skills. I always wonder if my English would sound like "example-based machine translation".ありがとう！ NileCat
Posts: 1168Joined: Sat 08.01.2009 2:11 pmLocation: Tokyo
Native language: Japanese
