Re: Could I ask you a favor?
by NileCat » Sat 10.02.2010 2:38 pm Thanks SakeIt2Me!I see exactly what you mean.As you know, "I understand it" does not necessarily mean "I will be able to use it properly", though. I know so-called "conjunction and syndeton" are ones of my weak points. Since the logic of structuring a sentence is totally different in Japanese, I often mix them up.Please keep your eyes on my posts! NileCat
Posts: 1168Joined: Sat 08.01.2009 2:11 pmLocation: Tokyo
